net.sourceforge.seqware.common.metadata
Class MetadataNoConnection

java.lang.Object
  net.sourceforge.seqware.common.metadata.Metadata
      net.sourceforge.seqware.common.metadata.MetadataNoConnection
All Implemented Interfaces:
MetadataInterface
public class MetadataNoConnection
extends Metadata

MetadataNoConnection class.

Version:
$Id: $Id
Author:
boconnor@oicr.on.ca This Metadata object essentially does nothing. It returns null, 0, or a successful ReturnValue for all methods. This lets us do absolutely no metadata writeback with objects that expect a validate Metadata object. Keep in mind this may break code that assumes it's talking to a Database- or WebService-backed Metadata object!

getChildSamplesFrom

public List<Sample> getChildSamplesFrom(int parentSampleAccession)
Description copied from interface: MetadataInterface
Get the child samples of a parent sample. These samples are further down the sample hierarchy (more specific). For example, if the parent sample or donor is ABC_001, the child sample would be ABC_001_Ref for the reference (blood) sample from the donor.

Parameters:
parentSampleAccession - the sw_accession of the parent sample / donor
Returns:
a list of child samples.
